The Russians warned of fake calls from banks
In Russia, the number of calls from fraudsters who replace the bank's phone number has increased.
This is reported by "Kommersant" with reference to the data of the Central Bank.
In the summer of 2019, the regulator gave telecom operators information about more than 2.5 thousand numbers, from which customers of various financial organizations called.
In 189 cases, operators found a substitution of the number.
Another 218 numbers were blocked, and in 59 cases a restriction on the use of financial services was set.
Deputy head of the Department of information security of the Central Bank Artem Sychev said that a wide range of Russian banks faced the substitution of the number.
He explained that operators do not always respond to the Central Bank's warnings about fraudulent calls, citing the lack of such a duty in the law "On communication."
In the bank "Otkritie," Rosbank and Alfa-Bank confirmed information about the increase in the number of fraudulent calls with the replacement of the number.
As reported in the press service of "Beeline," part of the information about the fraudulent calls, which was transmitted to the Central Bank, was incorrect: the lists included numbers that are really used by banks to communicate with customers.
Their blocking would cause failures in the work of the organization.
Artem Sychev said that the Central Bank plans to create a database of numbers of fraudsters, to which the telecom operator will contact at each call to check the number.
He explained that the establishment of such a base would require amendments to the legislation.
