As it became known to Parliamentskaya Gazeta, on September 27, Chairman of the Federation Council Committee on Economic Policy Andrey Kutepov sent a letter to the Minister of Economic Development Maxim Oreshkin and Finance Minister Anton Siluanov with a proposal to express a position on the initiatives of the subjects of the Federation on improving legislation in the field of support for small and medium-sized businesses (SMEs).
It's time to build interregional ties
The Committee of the Federation Council on Economic Policy summarized information received from the regions on the existing programs for the development of business and legalization of self-employed, as well as the results of such programs.
In their letters, the regions told the senators about the problems of the development of SMEs and sent proposals to improve the current legislation.
"To date, communication between the regions is not sufficiently established, as a result of which the business community in all regions of the visit by senators was identified the issue of the lack of information about regional entrepreneurship development programs in the country as a whole," said Andrey Kutepov.
In the annex to the letter, which was sent to the Government, he presented a set of positive developments of the regions on the legalization of self-employment and summary data from the regions with proposals and problems (available at the disposal of the editorial board).
In addition to the relevant ministries, the summary data from the regions were also sent to the heads of regional executive bodies.
The exchange of information on positively implemented developments in the regions could give impetus to the development of entrepreneurship in general.
The first step to such an exchange will be the direction of information available to the Committee on Economic Policy," the senator told the Parliament newspaper.
Useful experience
Today, in many regions of the country, programs to support small and medium-sized businesses are being implemented and are successfully operating.
For example, in the Vologda region, there is a Center for Entrepreneurship Support, which, in addition to financial support measures, assists businessmen in certifying finished products.
In the Ivanovo region, a business support system has been developed, providing for the implementation of the principle of one window through multifunctional centers.
In the Krasnodar region, beginning agricultural consumer cooperatives are provided with grants at the expense of the regional budget.
In the Oryol region, a center for cluster development is functioning.
The Amur region within the framework of the federal project "Acceleration of small and medium-sized businesses" provides for the possibility of subsidizing business incubators created on the basis of existing non-state coworking centers at the expense of the federal budget.
And in a number of other regions, special support measures are being taken for youth entrepreneurship.
Self-employed continue to get out of the shadows
According to the regional authorities, a number of changes to the current legislation should be made to more effectively support for small and medium-sized businesses.
For example, the Arkhangelsk region proposed to replace the term "self-employment" with "entrepreneurial activity," since this "most corresponds to the content of the state service to promote the self-employment of unemployed citizens."
In the Ivanovo region, it is necessary to make amendments to expand the list of activities provided by self-employed citizens, including activities for the finishing and repair of residential premises, country buildings, physical training.
The Bryansk region considers it important to strengthen control over unscrupulous dairy producers with the help of the veterinary system "Mercury."
And in the Kostroma and Magadan regions, they advocate the consolidation in the regulatory and legal field of the concept of "social entrepreneurship" and areas of support for social entrepreneurship.
All proposals from the regions will be taken into account in the preparation of state programs to support small and medium-sized businesses, and the most important will be developed in the form of specific bills.
"All proposals from the regions will be taken into account in the preparation of state programs to support small and medium-sized businesses, and the most important will be developed in the form of specific bills," - said Andrey Kutepov.
