The supply of the "sanctions" to Russia fell 100 times
The Russian government estimated that the supply of agricultural products and food to Russia from the countries that came under the Russian food embargo has decreased by more than 100 times since 2013.
According to the report sent to Russian President Vladimir Putin, in the first half of 2019, 31 thousand were imported from the sanctions countries. tons of products against 3 million 442.2 thousand. tons for the same period in 2013, reports "Interfax."
At the same time, the cost of imported products decreased to $ 226,5 million from $4 billion, 975,5 million, respectively.
We are talking about the supply of goods that were not subject to the embargo.
As indicated in the report, the volumes of prohibited products were compensated by increased imports from the CIS countries, Africa, Southeast Asia, Serbia.
Recall that at the end of August, the government extended until December 31, 2020 the period of validity of the rules for the destruction of agricultural products, raw materials and food, which are prohibited for import into Russia in the framework of counter-sanctions.
The document, posted on the official portal of legal information, noted that the validity of the rules was extended for another year - from December 31, 2019 to December 31, 2020.
Initially, the order to destroy the sanctions extended to products from the United States, the EU, Australia, Norway and Canada.
Later, from 13 August 2015, Albania, Montenegro, Iceland, Liechtenstein, from January 1, 2016 to "joined" this list.
The decree signed by Putin on the destruction of the smuggling "sanctions" (products that were under the food embargo, which Moscow imposed in response to anti-Russian sanctions of the West) entered into force in 2015.
In turn, the government allowed the destruction of "sanctions" food in any legal way.
As Western sanctions persisted, Russia also extended its response.
At the same time, this measure does not apply to products that citizens are imported for personal use.
The ban does not apply to the importation of goods for personal consumption weighing up to 5 kilograms.
However, the head of the Council under the President of the Russian Federation for the development of civil society and human rights Mikhail Fedotov previously called "just immoral" the destruction of food, and this, according to him, negatively affects the education of people.
Moreover, with the initiative to ban the destruction of food suitable for use, Rospotrebnadzor spoke in early June.
After that, a similar recommendation was made to the government by the Human Rights Council under the President of the Russian Federation.
And Deputy Prime Minister of the Russian Federation Alexei Gordeev said that it is wrong to destroy food, and it is necessary to think how to use them as intended, assessing the quality.
The head of the company was found guilty of tax evasion
By the verdict of the Leninsky District Court of Cheboksary, the director of Land and Law LLC Vyacheslav Morozov was found guilty of committing crimes under paragraph 1. "B" h. 2 st. 199 of the Criminal Code of the Russian Federation (tax evasion from the organization by including in the tax return knowingly false information, committed in a particularly large amount) and h. 2 st. 327 of the Criminal Code of the Russian Federation (forgery of an official document granting the rights and exempting from duties, for the purpose of its use, committed in order to conceal another crime and facilitate its commission).
This is reported by the press service of the Investigative Department of the Investigative Committee for Chuvashia.
From January 2008 to December 2009, Vyacheslav Morozov entered information about imperfect transactions in the documents of the tax accounting of LLC.
According to fictitious documents, the company incurred additional costs, and, therefore, the amount of taxes on added value and profit of the organization were reduced.
Vyacheslav Morozov was sentenced to 3.5 years in prison conditionally.
